Package cliapp.cliclient

Class CLIClient

java.lang.Object
cliapp.cliclient.CLIClient
public class CLIClient extends Object
CLIClient is a class that implements command-line interaction with the user. It contains Command objects and methods for their execution. It provides input and output, commands resolving and execution, exception processing, and other shell stuff.

    • getTrigger

      public String getTrigger(String trigger) throws CommandNotFoundError
      Find a trigger in the registered commands map by a full word or prefix if fuzzy mode is enabled.
      Parameters:
      trigger - the trigger for the command
      Returns:
      the trigger associated with the command
      Throws:
      CommandNotFoundError - if the command is not found

    • parseInlineParams

      public List<String> parseInlineParams(String line)
      Split the user input line into separated, non-empty parameters. Parameters in quotes are matched as one parameter.
      Parameters:
      line - the user input line
      Returns:
      a list of separated words

    • mapStaticRequirements

      public Map<String,String> mapStaticRequirements(List<Requirement<?,?>> staticRequirements, List<String> inlineParams) throws InlineParamsError
      Map static requirement names to specified inline parameters.
      Parameters:
      staticRequirements - a list of static requirements to map
      inlineParams - a list of inline parameters to map to the requirements
      Returns:
      a map where the key is the requirement name and the value is the inline parameter
      Throws:
      InlineParamsError - if the number of static requirements and inline parameters do not match

    • runClient

      public void runClient()
      Run an infinite loop for command line interaction. Waits for user input and tries to resolve and execute a command.
